Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing after revocation, his probation having been revoked effective 10-17-17.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of forty-two (42) months.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program but not the Challenge Incarceration Program.   Defendant is entitled to 121 days sentence credit.   
Minutes.

State moves to delete the penalty enhancer of 2nd or subsequent offense on count 1.   Motion granted.     
Count 1 - Possess Heroin - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, possess drug paraphernalia as repeater.   Motion granted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through counseling; 
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain full-time work/school combination; 
5) Spend five (5) days in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 04-05-16 at 6:00 p.m.
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) Submit DNA sample.   
Minutes.
